{{Quote|The jamming is still in place, of course, so we can't get any more information. But our sensors just picked up a huge jolt of repulsor activity coming from Drall. Unfocused, uncontrolled, but it's there. The Drallists have got the thing working.''"''<br />''"''I don't believe it. I can't believe it. The Selonians, maybe. They're good at underground work. The Overden has some good technicians. But the Drallists? They were never anything.|[[Brimon Yarar]] and [[Thrackan Sal-Solo]]|<ref name="Showdown at Centerpoint">''[[Showdown at Centerpoint]]''</ref>}}
The '''Drallist Front''', also known as simply the '''Drallists''' were an extremist political faction on [[Drall (planet)|Drall]]. During the [[Corellian Crisis|First Corellian Insurrection]] they seized power. The faction was relatively weak in itself, being little more than a subsidiary of the [[Sacorrian Triad]] and an ally of the [[Overden]] and the [[Human League]]. [[Anakin Solo]] indirectly destroyed them upon activating Drall's [[planetary repulsor]].<ref name="Showdown at Centerpoint" />

